# Targeted profiling on bugs and spikes (mandatory)

**Status:** User preference 2026-07-24 (§9.5). **§8.16** in AGENTS.md.

## When this applies

User reports **버그**, **버벅임**, **스파이크**, **멈춤**, **느림** — or an existing log (`app-spike/latest.md`, crash report, CPU 감시) points at a **specific area** of PIPBONG.

## Agent must do (same task — do not defer)

| Step | Action |
| ---- | ------ |
| 1 | Name the **subsystem** (UI refresh, multi-hold run, hotkey, capture/match, profile switch, overlay, input, …) |
| 2 | Add **opt-in** profiling for **that subsystem only** (default **OFF** — no daily-play overhead) |
| 3 | Write a **predictable report path** + short **Auto diagnosis** section (Korean bullets in report; plain Korean summary in chat per `brief-korean-replies.mdc`) |
| 4 | Document in **AGENTS.md §8.16** (and extend §8.x if a new pattern) **before closing** |
| 5 | Prefer **measure → fix → re-measure**; do not ship guess-only perf patches on multi-attempt bugs |

## Layering (do not duplicate)

| Layer | Use for |
| ----- | ------- |
| `AppSpikeProfiler` (§8.14) | Broad PIPBONG UI stall + session CPU — `app-spike/latest.md` |
| **Subsystem profiler** (this rule) | Narrow counters/timers/events for the **failing** code path |
| `CrashReporter` / `DiagnosticHub` | Light always-on breadcrumbs — not a substitute for repro profiling |

## Subsystem → profiling pattern (examples)

| Symptom / area | Targeted approach | Typical report / tags |
| -------------- | ----------------- | --------------------- |
| PIPBONG UI lag, multi-hold | Extend `AppSpikeProfiler` events or scoped timers on `applyRunUiState`, fast-repeat flush, feature-list batch | `gui_stall_*` crumbs, `sessions=N` |
| Hotkey miss / Alt+Tab | Opt-in hook-path timing or latch-state log; tag `hotkey_*` | `diagnostics/hotkey/latest.md` or app-spike events |
| ImageFind slow / miss | Per-poll capture+match ms; tag `imagefind_poll` | app-spike or block-run feedback columns |
| Profile switch jank / ping-pong | `ProfileSwitchProfiler` on `requestAutoProfileSwitch` / `executeProfileSwitch` | `profile-switch/latest.md`, `scripts/analyze-profile-switch.ps1` |
| Overlay / capture pick | Teardown order + BitBlt duration | `overlay_pick` events |
| Input / modifier drop | Session key tracking audit (no blind KEYUP) | policy sim + manual checklist §8.6 |

New subsystem: pick a **single** opt-in setting key `program/<area>Profiling` or env `PIPBONG_<AREA>_PROFILE=1` when a program-settings toggle is warranted.

## Report rules

- Repo path: `app-spike/latest.md` **or** `diagnostics/<subsystem>/latest.md` (+ AppData mirror under `%LOCALAPPDATA%/PIPBONG/PIPBONG/…`)
- Include: `format`, `session_seconds`, **Auto diagnosis** (Korean), summary counters, optional event TSV
- Optional script: `scripts/analyze-<subsystem>.ps1` when reports are non-trivial

## Anti-patterns

- Closing a perf/spike bug task with **only** a code change and **no** way to re-measure
- Always-on heavy sampling in hot paths (hooks, 4 ms loops) without opt-in
- Asking the user to paste workflow JSON or manually grep logs when the agent can add profiling
- Replacing §8.14 broad profiler with a one-off `qDebug` spam

